==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polysyllable
<hw>Pol"y*syl`la*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>syllable</ets>.]</ety> <def>A word of many
syllables, or consisting of more syllables than three; -- words of less
than four syllables being called <contr>monosyllables</contr>,
<contr>dissyllables</contr>, and <contr>trisyllables</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polysyndetic</ent>⟦br⟧
